An example using Microsoft's WiX with NAnt during an automated build process to generate a deployable MSI file

<a href="http://wix.sourceforge.net/">Offical Website</a>

<a href="http://wix.sourceforge.net/manual-wix2/wix_index.htm">Schema information,etc.</a>

<a href="http://www.tramontana.co.hu/wix/">Still the best tutorial</a>

NOTES:

1. Requires MSI Installer be installed on what ever box you plan to test deployment on.

2. I run <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/en-us/msi/setup/msival2_exe.asp">MsiVal2.exe</a> (including in source lib folder in trunk) against the created MSI to see if we violate any of <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa369206.aspx">Microsoft's Internal Consistency Evaluators(ICE</a>)
